1
00:00:01,502 --> 00:00:03,304
Jotaro: Before we
get things started,

2
00:00:03,337 --> 00:00:04,939
there’s something I wanna check.

3
00:00:04,972 --> 00:00:07,808
How about you go ahead
and shuffle those cards?

4
00:00:07,841 --> 00:00:09,676
♪

5
00:00:19,987 --> 00:00:22,356
D’arby: And shuffled, they are.

6
00:00:22,389 --> 00:00:24,791
what, pray tell,
do you have in mind next?

7
00:00:24,825 --> 00:00:27,528
Jotaro: Now draw a card
from the deck.

8
00:00:27,561 --> 00:00:31,331
Which one it is doesn’t really
make a whole lot of difference,

9
00:00:31,365 --> 00:00:33,534
but don’t show anyone.

10
00:00:33,567 --> 00:00:35,602
( D’arby scoffs )

11
00:00:35,636 --> 00:00:37,037
Very well.

12
00:00:37,070 --> 00:00:38,838
Jotaro: And now i’ll call it.

13
00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:40,507
It’s the six of hearts.

14
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:43,344
Next, I think i’ll name
the cards from the top down.

15
00:00:43,377 --> 00:00:45,446
Five of spades,
queen of diamonds,

16
00:00:45,479 --> 00:00:47,448
Jack of spades,
ace of hearts,

17
00:00:47,481 --> 00:00:49,750
seven of diamonds,
plus the six of clubs,

18
00:00:49,783 --> 00:00:51,752
king of clubs,
and two of diamonds.

19
00:00:51,785 --> 00:00:52,786
( D’arby grunts )

20
00:00:53,921 --> 00:00:56,123
( Avdol gasps )
He guessed them all!

21
00:00:56,156 --> 00:00:58,592
and that’s
after d’arby shuffled the deck!

22
00:00:58,625 --> 00:01:00,127
How did you do that?!

23
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:04,031
Jotaro: I could rattle off
the entire deck if I wanted to.

24
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:05,766
Remember my request
from earlier?

25
00:01:05,799 --> 00:01:07,601
while you
were shuffling the cards,

26
00:01:07,634 --> 00:01:08,702
star platinum was busy

27
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,136
memorizing their order
in the deck.

28
00:01:11,605 --> 00:01:13,674
d’arby: Quite
the interesting strategy.

29
00:01:13,707 --> 00:01:15,008
That said, defeating your plan

30
00:01:15,042 --> 00:01:17,411
is a simple matter
of shuffling the cards

31
00:01:17,444 --> 00:01:19,546
in a manner that obstructs
your vision of them.

32
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:21,549
Jotaro: Are you that dense?

33
00:01:21,582 --> 00:01:23,717
Cheating is gonna be
damn near impossible

34
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:25,885
as long as you have me
as an opponent.

35
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,954
Just somethin’ I thought
you should be aware of.

36
00:01:27,988 --> 00:01:30,757
( D’arby grunts )
okay.

37
00:01:36,163 --> 00:01:38,165
♪

38
00:01:41,835 --> 00:01:43,970
Narrator: The security seal.

39
00:01:44,004 --> 00:01:46,874
an unbroken seal
is an irrefutable confirmation

40
00:01:46,907 --> 00:01:50,644
that the deck has not
been tampered with in any way.

41
00:01:51,845 --> 00:01:54,014
( Shuffles cards )

42
00:02:00,387 --> 00:02:02,189
jotaro: Well,
there’s only one joker here.

43
00:02:02,222 --> 00:02:04,624
Don’t see anything unusual.

44
00:02:04,658 --> 00:02:07,027
- It’s a normal deck.
- ( Avdol grunts )

45
00:02:10,564 --> 00:02:12,833
d’arby:
The page number is 538.

46
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:16,236
540. No, page 556.

47
00:02:17,704 --> 00:02:19,506
I’ve still got it.

48
00:02:19,540 --> 00:02:22,843
My ability to discern
page numbers by touch

49
00:02:22,876 --> 00:02:24,711
is as sharp as ever.

50
00:02:24,745 --> 00:02:27,147
it’s true
that jotaro’s star platinum

51
00:02:27,181 --> 00:02:29,083
has incredible visual prowess,

52
00:02:29,116 --> 00:02:31,585
but I can remember
the placement of anything

53
00:02:31,618 --> 00:02:33,620
simply through
the use of touch.

54
00:02:33,654 --> 00:02:35,122
Shuffle them all you want.

55
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:38,258
I still know the exact location
of every card.

56
00:02:45,232 --> 00:02:48,168
Okay, open the game.

57
00:02:50,637 --> 00:02:52,806
looks like
it’s the ten of hearts.

58
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,809
jotaro:
I drew the seven of cubs.

59
00:02:54,842 --> 00:02:56,911
D’arby: Then it seems
like i’ll be dealing.

60
00:02:56,944 --> 00:02:58,512
( Chuckles )
All right.

61
00:02:58,545 --> 00:03:01,915
i need to shuffle
so star platinum can’t see.

62
00:03:07,955 --> 00:03:09,957
If you would cut the deck...

63
00:03:22,703 --> 00:03:25,272
D’arby: Thank you,
and now i’ll deal.

64
00:03:26,573 --> 00:03:28,942
One for jotaro. One for me.

65
00:03:28,976 --> 00:03:32,112
One for jotaro. One for me.

66
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:36,717
( Screaming )

67
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:40,087
avdol: Huh?
I-I don’t understand!

68
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,555
What happened?!

69
00:03:41,588 --> 00:03:43,590
Jotaro, his finger!

70
00:03:43,624 --> 00:03:45,292
Why the devil would you
use star platinum

71
00:03:45,325 --> 00:03:47,127
to break d’arby’s finger?

72
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,962
Jotaro: Like I said,

73
00:03:48,996 --> 00:03:51,198
you’re not gonna cheat
while you’re playing against me.

74
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:53,100
Avdol: Huh? He tried to cheat?

75
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:55,636
But he was only dealing
the cards, wasn’t he?

76
00:03:55,669 --> 00:03:58,639
I didn’t notice him
do anything suspicious.

77
00:03:58,672 --> 00:04:00,140
Jotaro: That’s what
he wanted us to think,

78
00:04:00,174 --> 00:04:03,210
but take a good look
at the cards in his left hand.

79
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:05,011
Avdol: Ahh! I see now!

80
00:04:05,045 --> 00:04:07,014
The second card is sticking out.

81
00:04:07,047 --> 00:04:09,816
Jotaro: That’s the card
he tried to deal me.

82
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:12,953
the entire time, he was
pretending to deal the top card,

83
00:04:12,986 --> 00:04:15,155
but the truth is
he was dealing me

84
00:04:15,189 --> 00:04:16,791
the second card from the top.

85
00:04:16,823 --> 00:04:18,091
That being the case,

86
00:04:18,125 --> 00:04:21,629
it means the top card
would have gone to him.

87
00:04:21,662 --> 00:04:23,597
If he’d gotten his hands on it,

88
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:26,333
the cheating bastard would
have had a total of three tens.

89
00:04:26,366 --> 00:04:29,636
Narrator: This maneuver
is known as the second deal,

90
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:31,639
a devious
sleight-of-hand technique

91
00:04:31,672 --> 00:04:33,174
involving the dealer
throwing out

92
00:04:33,207 --> 00:04:35,176
the second card in the deck,

93
00:04:35,209 --> 00:04:38,879
instead of dealing the top card
as one would expect.

94
00:04:38,912 --> 00:04:41,681
when the technique
is executed by a professional,

95
00:04:41,715 --> 00:04:45,152
the cheat is almost undetectable
to the naked eye.

96
00:04:45,185 --> 00:04:47,788
And if that wasn’t enough,
d’arby can discern

97
00:04:47,821 --> 00:04:50,857
the location of every card
in the deck by touch.

98
00:04:50,891 --> 00:04:55,262
D’arby: You brutish imbecile!
How dare you break my finger?

99
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:57,030
( Gasps )

100
00:04:57,064 --> 00:04:59,233
Jotaro: I was playing nice
with that attack.

101
00:04:59,266 --> 00:05:02,102
You should count yourself lucky
I didn’t rip it off.

102
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:03,103
( D’arby grunting )

103
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:04,704
Jotaro: Ah, good grief.

104
00:05:04,738 --> 00:05:06,740
I guess I can’t let you
cut the deck anymore.

105
00:05:07,941 --> 00:05:10,777
someone else
is gonna do it from now on.

106
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:14,348
That boy on the hill
looks up to the job.

107
00:05:14,381 --> 00:05:16,950
( D’arby groans )
Have it your way.

108
00:05:16,984 --> 00:05:19,186
Jotaro: Hey, avdol,
ask him over.

109
00:05:19,219 --> 00:05:20,787
Avdol: Right away.

110
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:22,856
- D’arby: Most impressive.
- Avdol: Hmm?

111
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:24,091
D’arby: Successful cheating

112
00:05:24,124 --> 00:05:26,159
requires
the element of surprise,

113
00:05:26,193 --> 00:05:29,630
and it takes more
than sharp eyes to prevent that.

114
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:31,198
It appears I underestimated you,

115
00:05:31,231 --> 00:05:33,300
as you saw through
my second deal.

116
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:37,170
I’ll accept my fractured finger
as proper punishment.

117
00:05:37,204 --> 00:05:40,274
But from here on, i’ll devote
my full concentration

118
00:05:40,307 --> 00:05:43,377
to winning the game, jotaro.

119
00:05:43,410 --> 00:05:46,680
i’ve not done so
since my colossal gamble

120
00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:49,783
on may 17, 1986.
I was playing

121
00:05:49,816 --> 00:05:52,986
against a Japanese man
known as shozo mayama.

122
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:55,155
As the Victor,
my spoils included

123
00:05:55,189 --> 00:05:57,892
his eight Tokyo properties
and his soul.

124
00:05:57,925 --> 00:05:59,927
I will say this for mayama.

125
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:02,963
Wealth didn’t dull
his gambler’s instincts.

126
00:06:04,131 --> 00:06:06,133
It’s only fair that I warn you

127
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:08,402
i’m not here
on behalf of lord dio!

128
00:06:08,435 --> 00:06:11,438
I am here due to the simple fact
that I am a born gambler!

129
00:06:13,207 --> 00:06:15,109
Avdol: W-what do you
think you’re doing?

130
00:06:15,142 --> 00:06:17,077
Those souls are Mr. Joestar’s
and polnareff’s!

131
00:06:26,753 --> 00:06:27,887
( Both gasp )

132
00:06:27,921 --> 00:06:29,189
D’arby: I’ve done nothing more

133
00:06:29,223 --> 00:06:31,425
than split their souls
into six chips each.

134
00:06:31,458 --> 00:06:33,894
I’m sure you know this,
but in poker,

135
00:06:33,927 --> 00:06:36,029
if you’re
on the verge of losing,

136
00:06:36,063 --> 00:06:37,998
it’s perfectly acceptable
to fold.

137
00:06:38,031 --> 00:06:41,167
However, if you use up
all the chips for the ante,

138
00:06:41,201 --> 00:06:44,004
there’s no way to bet,
and the game doesn’t work.

139
00:06:44,037 --> 00:06:46,806
To put it plainly,
winning back six chips

140
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:49,876
is the equivalent of winning
the soul of one of your friends.

141
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:51,478
Make sense?

142
00:06:51,512 --> 00:06:54,982
All right then, jotaro,
if you still want to play,

143
00:06:55,015 --> 00:06:57,885
you’ll have the opportunity
to win back the chips,

144
00:06:57,918 --> 00:07:02,289
but before that, I need
to hear you say the words.

145
00:07:04,124 --> 00:07:05,392
Jotaro: With pleasure.

146
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:07,861
I’ll bet my soul
on the game’s outcome.

147
00:07:07,895 --> 00:07:08,996
D’arby: Okay.

148
00:07:09,029 --> 00:07:10,397
Avdol: Jotaro!

149
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:15,803
D’arby: The pure white chips
in front of you

150
00:07:15,836 --> 00:07:18,005
are a physical representation
of your soul.

151
00:07:18,038 --> 00:07:20,741
Once i’ve procured
all six of those chips,

152
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:24,144
your soul will be added
to my collection.

153
00:07:27,748 --> 00:07:29,883
♪

154
00:07:29,917 --> 00:07:32,753
( D’arby chuckles )

155
00:07:38,091 --> 00:07:41,061
For my opening action,
I shall bet one chip

156
00:07:41,094 --> 00:07:43,163
of polnareff’s soul.
( Chuckles )

157
00:07:44,198 --> 00:07:46,067
Let’s begin.

158
00:07:46,099 --> 00:07:47,934
Narrator: When beginning
a new game of poker,

159
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:50,904
each player is dealt
a total of five cards.

160
00:07:50,938 --> 00:07:54,108
Players can improve their hand
by swapping out cards.

161
00:07:56,710 --> 00:07:58,845
Though it seems straightforward
on the surface,

162
00:07:58,879 --> 00:08:01,215
it’s the betting aspect
that makes poker

163
00:08:01,248 --> 00:08:04,118
a game of determination
and psychology.

164
00:08:05,152 --> 00:08:06,987
D’arby: Now then, what to do?

165
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:08,588
Ah, I think i’ll raise.

166
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:13,527
Jotaro, you should bear in mind

167
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:16,530
that those six chips beside you
are your soul.

168
00:08:16,563 --> 00:08:19,599
Make sure you think carefully
before making a move.

169
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:21,201
- Boy: Eh?
- Avdol: Listen.

170
00:08:21,235 --> 00:08:24,071
It’s okay if you don’t
understand what’s going on.

171
00:08:24,104 --> 00:08:25,172
Don’t worry yourself.

172
00:08:25,205 --> 00:08:26,840
You just focus your attention

173
00:08:26,874 --> 00:08:29,110
on cutting and dealing
the cards, all right?

174
00:08:29,142 --> 00:08:30,110
Boy: Uh, mm.

175
00:08:30,143 --> 00:08:32,312
Jotaro: Give me three cards.

176
00:08:32,346 --> 00:08:34,815
♪

177
00:08:39,319 --> 00:08:42,222
D’arby: Would you look at that?
Such a serious glare.

178
00:08:42,256 --> 00:08:45,626
Behind it must be
an outstanding hand.

179
00:08:45,659 --> 00:08:47,895
i suppose
i’ll play it safe for now

180
00:08:47,928 --> 00:08:49,630
and bet one more polnareff.

181
00:08:49,663 --> 00:08:51,231
Jotaro: Call, one.

182
00:08:51,265 --> 00:08:52,900
Avdol: If you don’t fold,

183
00:08:52,933 --> 00:08:55,836
you’ll need three chips
per game, at the very least.

184
00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:58,338
D’arby: All right,
bring it on, jotaro.

185
00:09:00,674 --> 00:09:03,210
Jotaro: Two pair,
with eights and nines.

186
00:09:03,243 --> 00:09:04,845
D’arby: Hmm.

187
00:09:04,878 --> 00:09:06,213
That’s too bad.

188
00:09:06,246 --> 00:09:09,015
Two pair, Jacks and queens.

189
00:09:10,017 --> 00:09:11,619
( Avdol gasps )
oh, no!

190
00:09:11,652 --> 00:09:13,621
d’arby: My,
that was a close one.

191
00:09:13,654 --> 00:09:16,123
I was on the verge
of a crushing defeat.

192
00:09:16,156 --> 00:09:17,257
( Laughs )

193
00:09:18,892 --> 00:09:21,061
But as it stands...

194
00:09:21,094 --> 00:09:23,363
♪

195
00:09:25,299 --> 00:09:26,934
( Laughs )

196
00:09:29,369 --> 00:09:31,738
Avdol: H-he only has three left.

197
00:09:31,772 --> 00:09:34,341
Jotaro, what are you...

198
00:09:34,374 --> 00:09:37,644
Jotaro: Okay, next game.
deal the cards.

199
00:09:37,678 --> 00:09:40,214
♪

200
00:09:45,118 --> 00:09:47,954
d’arby: You should
be careful what you wish for.

201
00:09:47,988 --> 00:09:50,657
the next game
may well be your last.

202
00:09:50,691 --> 00:09:51,759
( Chuckles )

203
00:09:55,796 --> 00:09:58,032
I’ll change one card.

204
00:09:58,065 --> 00:09:59,066
Huh?

205
00:10:04,671 --> 00:10:05,705
( Grunts )

206
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:09,176
Boy: Huh?

207
00:10:10,811 --> 00:10:12,379
d’arby:
What’s the problem, jotaro?

208
00:10:12,412 --> 00:10:14,314
Hurry up, and check your hand

209
00:10:14,348 --> 00:10:17,852
so you can make a decision as to
whether you’ll change or fold.

210
00:10:17,885 --> 00:10:19,754
Avdol: Hey, jotaro?

211
00:10:21,088 --> 00:10:22,356
Jotaro: No, it’s fine.

212
00:10:23,891 --> 00:10:25,159
These cards will do.

213
00:10:25,192 --> 00:10:27,261
- Avdol: Wha?!
- Boy: Eh?

214
00:10:27,294 --> 00:10:29,396
D’arby: So sorry. Come again?

215
00:10:29,429 --> 00:10:32,399
There must be some confusion.
Perhaps I misheard you.

216
00:10:32,432 --> 00:10:35,669
I could have sworn I heard
you say, "these cards will do."

217
00:10:35,702 --> 00:10:38,872
Jotaro: No, you heard right.
I’m fine with these cards.

218
00:10:38,906 --> 00:10:40,908
I’ll play the round
with this hand.

219
00:10:40,941 --> 00:10:42,709
- D’arby: Obviously!
- ( Slams table )

220
00:10:42,743 --> 00:10:45,679
What i’m trying to ask is do
you intend to play those cards

221
00:10:45,712 --> 00:10:47,280
without so much
as glancing at them?!

222
00:10:48,415 --> 00:10:50,083
Jotaro: These cards will do.

223
00:10:50,117 --> 00:10:52,720
D’arby: Enough subterfuge!
Answer me!

224
00:10:52,753 --> 00:10:55,356
How can you play a round
with any sort of confidence

225
00:10:55,389 --> 00:10:58,192
if you don’t even look
at the cards in your hand?!

226
00:10:58,225 --> 00:11:00,127
Jotaro: Need a favor. You in?

227
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,395
- ( D’arby growls )
- Avdol: Favor?

228
00:11:01,428 --> 00:11:03,330
of course,
but answer something first.

229
00:11:03,363 --> 00:11:06,166
why are you hellbent
on not looking at your cards?

230
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:09,036
D’arby: Damn it, jotaro!
I demand that you answer me!

231
00:11:09,069 --> 00:11:11,872
Jotaro: Let’s see now.
Raise you another two.

232
00:11:15,209 --> 00:11:18,312
And while i’m at it,
i’ll throw in avdol’s soul.

233
00:11:18,345 --> 00:11:21,181
D’arby: Argh! What?!

234
00:11:21,215 --> 00:11:23,250
( Growls )

235
00:11:23,283 --> 00:11:26,720
avdol: I admit you’re
an impressive opponent, d’arby.

236
00:11:26,753 --> 00:11:29,256
Sure, you’re no match
for our stands physically,

237
00:11:29,289 --> 00:11:30,390
but under pressure,

238
00:11:30,424 --> 00:11:32,860
you can be
amazingly calm and clever.

239
00:11:32,893 --> 00:11:36,196
Suffice it to say, i’m not much
in terms of being a gambler.

240
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:39,233
It’d be easy for you
to read me like a book,

241
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:41,835
so I could never defeat
someone like you,

242
00:11:41,869 --> 00:11:44,271
but I have
the utmost confidence in jotaro.

243
00:11:44,304 --> 00:11:46,973
i don’t know why
he won’t look at his cards,

244
00:11:47,007 --> 00:11:48,442
but that’s none of my concern.

245
00:11:48,475 --> 00:11:50,177
If he asks for my soul,

246
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:53,046
i won’t hesitate
to put my life on the line.

247
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:55,683
My soul is in jotaro’s
more than capable hands.

248
00:11:55,716 --> 00:11:59,019
D’arby: So that’s
how we’re playing this.

249
00:12:01,255 --> 00:12:03,758
It’s become apparent
that the two of you

250
00:12:03,790 --> 00:12:06,326
have succumbed to the pressure
of our little game.

251
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:09,296
You there, I believe
you owe me another card.

252
00:12:09,329 --> 00:12:10,497
Hurry, and deal me.

253
00:12:10,531 --> 00:12:11,832
Boy: Y-yes, sir.

254
00:12:17,004 --> 00:12:18,005
D’arby: Hmm.

255
00:12:19,806 --> 00:12:22,876
boy: I dealt just
as you asked, master d’arby.

256
00:12:22,910 --> 00:12:26,447
His hand is worthless.
There’s no doubt about it.

257
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:29,483
My skills as a dealer
never fail.

258
00:12:29,516 --> 00:12:32,886
You’ve won. I know you have.

259
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:34,355
D’arby: Jotaro’s
under the assumption

260
00:12:34,388 --> 00:12:36,924
the boy has nothing
to do with this,

261
00:12:36,957 --> 00:12:39,259
but little does he know
everyone in this cafe

262
00:12:39,293 --> 00:12:41,896
and within sight of this place
works for me...

263
00:12:42,963 --> 00:12:45,499
Even the bartender
and those men.

264
00:12:45,532 --> 00:12:47,834
No matter what, I can’t fail,

265
00:12:47,868 --> 00:12:51,372
as my directive is to make sure
jotaro’s hand is weak.

266
00:12:51,405 --> 00:12:54,975
Still, not looking at the cards
was a bold move.

267
00:12:55,008 --> 00:12:58,311
He caught me by surprise,
albeit briefly.

268
00:12:58,345 --> 00:13:02,316
it’s clearly a bluff.
How dare he bluff against me?

269
00:13:02,349 --> 00:13:06,019
Does the fool really think
i’ll lie down and fold?

270
00:13:06,053 --> 00:13:08,322
Hah! Very well.

271
00:13:08,355 --> 00:13:09,890
If that’s your game,

272
00:13:09,923 --> 00:13:14,060
i’ll match you
with six polnareffs, and...

273
00:13:14,094 --> 00:13:16,430
I raise you joseph’s soul.

274
00:13:16,463 --> 00:13:19,533
What do you think?
15 chips total.

275
00:13:19,566 --> 00:13:20,934
( Both gasp )

276
00:13:20,968 --> 00:13:22,503
Avdol: What?! Hold on a minute!

277
00:13:22,536 --> 00:13:24,571
that’s not fair!
How can you raise your ante

278
00:13:24,605 --> 00:13:27,108
when jotaro doesn’t have
any more chips?

279
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:28,842
d’arby:
He’s out of chips, you say?

280
00:13:28,876 --> 00:13:30,378
There’s an easy way to fix that.

281
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:31,978
Avdol: What do you mean?

282
00:13:32,012 --> 00:13:34,147
d’arby: Rectifying
your chip conundrum is simple

283
00:13:34,181 --> 00:13:37,017
as long as my stand
has a written contract.

284
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:38,418
Once the deal is done,

285
00:13:38,452 --> 00:13:40,387
it’ll have carte blanche
to take a soul.

286
00:13:40,420 --> 00:13:42,589
Avdol: And exactly whose soul
are you talking about?!

287
00:13:42,623 --> 00:13:45,526
( D’arby chuckles )
Kakyoin’s in the hospital.

288
00:13:45,559 --> 00:13:48,295
Why don’t you
simply bet his soul?

289
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:49,296
Avdol: What?!

290
00:13:49,329 --> 00:13:50,997
D’arby: Panic, fool.

291
00:13:51,031 --> 00:13:53,066
Show me your doubt and fear.

292
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:55,903
Let me see you lose
that cool composure.

293
00:13:55,936 --> 00:13:58,605
How dare he try to bluff me?

294
00:13:58,639 --> 00:14:01,375
After i’m finished with him,
that poker face

295
00:14:01,408 --> 00:14:04,244
will be a contorted ball
of anguish and misery.

296
00:14:04,278 --> 00:14:06,213
Jotaro: Sounds like a plan.

297
00:14:07,548 --> 00:14:09,350
I’ll see your bet
with kakyoin’s soul.

298
00:14:09,383 --> 00:14:12,119
( D’arby gasps )

299
00:14:12,152 --> 00:14:14,054
Avdol: Wait! Jotaro, you can’t!

300
00:14:14,087 --> 00:14:17,223
Betting a man’s soul without
his knowledge is so uncouth!

301
00:14:17,257 --> 00:14:19,292
Jotaro: Well,
it is kinda selfish.

302
00:14:19,326 --> 00:14:20,460
( D’arby gasps )

303
00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:24,898
hey, jotaro,
what did you just do?!

304
00:14:24,932 --> 00:14:28,202
Jotaro: What did I just do?
What do you mean by that?

305
00:14:28,235 --> 00:14:29,670
D’arby: You lit a cigare--

306
00:14:29,703 --> 00:14:32,339
( groans )

307
00:14:32,372 --> 00:14:35,942
Jotaro: What’s wrong with you?
Not feeling well or something?

308
00:14:39,079 --> 00:14:40,948
D’arby: Impertinent--

309
00:14:40,981 --> 00:14:43,083
why is he so confident?

310
00:14:43,116 --> 00:14:46,252
could he have--
could he have used star platinum

311
00:14:46,286 --> 00:14:48,555
to swap the cards
without my knowing?

312
00:14:51,992 --> 00:14:54,328
♪

313
00:15:02,336 --> 00:15:05,539
( Boy panting )

314
00:15:05,572 --> 00:15:07,541
( D’arby groans )
Stupid brat.

315
00:15:07,574 --> 00:15:09,076
What are you thinking?

316
00:15:09,109 --> 00:15:11,478
don’t look at me
with that worried grimace

317
00:15:11,512 --> 00:15:15,683
if jotaro finds out you work
for me, i’ll murder you.

318
00:15:15,716 --> 00:15:17,718
( Gasping )

319
00:15:20,721 --> 00:15:23,657
Compose yourself.
I have four kings.

320
00:15:23,690 --> 00:15:27,127
The only hands that could
beat me are four aces,

321
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:31,965
a straight flush,
or a joker-led five of a kind.

322
00:15:31,999 --> 00:15:34,301
In order to get his mitts
on any of those hands,

323
00:15:34,334 --> 00:15:37,304
jotaro would have to switch
all five cards,

324
00:15:37,337 --> 00:15:39,306
a challenge, indeed.

325
00:15:39,339 --> 00:15:41,041
With star platinum’s speed,

326
00:15:41,074 --> 00:15:44,578
there’s a chance he could have
switched a card, but five?

327
00:15:44,611 --> 00:15:49,182
could he really do that
right under my nose? Impossible.

328
00:15:49,216 --> 00:15:52,720
There’s no way I could have
missed him replacing all five.

329
00:15:52,753 --> 00:15:56,490
I’m the great d’arby,
the king of games,

330
00:15:56,523 --> 00:15:58,725
master at the art of gambling.

331
00:15:58,759 --> 00:16:03,230
I’ve had enough of this, jotaro.
Your time has come.

332
00:16:03,263 --> 00:16:06,032
He lit that cigarette
to psych me out,

333
00:16:06,066 --> 00:16:08,802
so now I know he’s bluffing.
( Gasps )

334
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,508
Ah, you’re kidding me?!

335
00:16:14,541 --> 00:16:16,076
You got a drink, too?!

336
00:16:16,109 --> 00:16:18,078
When did you have a chance to--

337
00:16:18,111 --> 00:16:20,747
you bastard!
How dare you make fun of me?!

338
00:16:20,781 --> 00:16:21,749
Let’s finish this!

339
00:16:21,782 --> 00:16:23,284
My hand is unbeata--

340
00:16:23,317 --> 00:16:24,351
jotaro: Hold it!

341
00:16:24,384 --> 00:16:26,286
Why are you jumping the gun

342
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:28,355
when I haven’t
raised the pot yet?

343
00:16:28,388 --> 00:16:29,589
- ( D’arby gasps )
- ( Boy gasps )

344
00:16:29,623 --> 00:16:32,359
- ( Avdol gasps )
- ( D’arby trills )

345
00:16:32,392 --> 00:16:34,127
Raise the pot?! No!

346
00:16:34,161 --> 00:16:36,130
You don’t have anything
to raise it with!

347
00:16:38,765 --> 00:16:41,067
( Jotaro exhales )
That’s where you’re wrong.

348
00:16:41,101 --> 00:16:43,337
i’ll raise you
with my mother’s soul.

349
00:16:43,370 --> 00:16:45,339
D’arby: What?!

350
00:16:45,372 --> 00:16:47,241
Avdol: Are you
out of your mind?!

351
00:16:47,274 --> 00:16:49,476
Jotaro, why would you bet
your mother’s soul?!

352
00:16:49,510 --> 00:16:51,512
♪

353
00:16:54,081 --> 00:16:55,583
Jotaro: The entire reason
i came to Egypt

354
00:16:55,616 --> 00:16:57,485
in the first place
was to save my mother,

355
00:16:57,518 --> 00:17:00,554
so if I end up losing here,
she’ll die anyway.

356
00:17:00,587 --> 00:17:02,489
She won’t mind
if I bet her soul.

357
00:17:02,523 --> 00:17:04,392
So then, d’arby, for your sake,

358
00:17:04,424 --> 00:17:07,761
I hope you have something to bet
that matches my mother’s soul.

359
00:17:07,794 --> 00:17:10,363
- ( D’arby panting )
- Jotaro: I know.

360
00:17:10,397 --> 00:17:11,765
For your ante,

361
00:17:11,798 --> 00:17:14,467
I want you to tell me
the secret of dio’s stand.

362
00:17:14,501 --> 00:17:16,603
( D’arby gasping )

363
00:17:19,606 --> 00:17:21,608
avdol:
Judging from his reaction,

364
00:17:21,642 --> 00:17:24,411
he indeed knows dio’s secret.

365
00:17:24,444 --> 00:17:25,745
Unfortunately for him,

366
00:17:25,779 --> 00:17:27,781
dio doesn’t take treason
sitting down.

367
00:17:27,814 --> 00:17:30,417
if he tells us
the information we want to know,

368
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:32,385
he’s as good as dead.

369
00:17:34,154 --> 00:17:36,356
Jotaro, if you’re
confident enough

370
00:17:36,390 --> 00:17:38,092
to bet your mother’s soul,

371
00:17:38,125 --> 00:17:40,628
you’re sure your hand
will win, aren’t you?

372
00:17:40,661 --> 00:17:43,230
You wouldn’t let us down,
would you?

373
00:17:43,263 --> 00:17:45,232
you’ve got
the winning hand, right?

374
00:17:45,265 --> 00:17:46,833
Jotaro?!

375
00:17:46,867 --> 00:17:49,236
( D’arby panting )

376
00:17:49,269 --> 00:17:52,172
( Boy gasping )

377
00:17:52,206 --> 00:17:54,141
( Jotaro spits )
come on!

378
00:17:54,174 --> 00:17:55,876
are you gonna
call my bluff or fold?!

379
00:17:55,909 --> 00:17:59,579
decision time!
Spit it out already! D’arby!

380
00:17:59,613 --> 00:18:01,381
( D’arby wails )

381
00:18:01,415 --> 00:18:04,184
( Gasping )

382
00:18:07,688 --> 00:18:10,224
( Laughs )

383
00:18:10,257 --> 00:18:11,692
I’ll say it.

384
00:18:11,725 --> 00:18:14,695
- ( Crazed laughter )
- ( Boy gasping )

385
00:18:14,728 --> 00:18:17,497
( Avdol panting )

386
00:18:17,531 --> 00:18:20,901
D’arby: I’ll say it, damn it!

387
00:18:20,934 --> 00:18:23,170
( Gasping )

388
00:18:25,205 --> 00:18:26,606
I’ll say it!

389
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:29,309
I’m the world’s
greatest gambler!

390
00:18:29,343 --> 00:18:32,313
I can do this. I’ll call!

391
00:18:34,381 --> 00:18:37,684
Call, call, call, call, call,

392
00:18:37,718 --> 00:18:40,487
call, call, call, call.

393
00:18:40,521 --> 00:18:44,825
I’m going to call!

394
00:18:44,858 --> 00:18:46,226
Ca--

395
00:18:48,262 --> 00:18:50,331
( gasping )

396
00:18:50,364 --> 00:18:52,933
C-c-c-c-c-ca--ca--

397
00:18:52,966 --> 00:18:55,268
( coughing )

398
00:18:55,302 --> 00:18:56,737
( Growls )

399
00:18:56,770 --> 00:18:59,373
( Groans )
C-c--

400
00:18:59,406 --> 00:19:02,242
( wails )

401
00:19:02,276 --> 00:19:03,244
( Both gasping )

402
00:19:03,277 --> 00:19:05,279
( D’arby coughs )

403
00:19:05,312 --> 00:19:07,447
C-c...

404
00:19:07,481 --> 00:19:09,516
( Wails )

405
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:11,752
( Gasps )
C-c--

406
00:19:11,785 --> 00:19:14,855
I can’t do it! I’m petrified!

407
00:19:14,888 --> 00:19:17,791
I’m too terrified
to say the words!

408
00:19:17,824 --> 00:19:20,860
C-c-c-ca--

409
00:19:20,894 --> 00:19:24,798
i--i can’t--
I can’t breathe.

410
00:19:24,832 --> 00:19:26,534
( Gasping )

411
00:19:26,567 --> 00:19:28,536
C-c-c-c--

412
00:19:28,569 --> 00:19:30,471
( gasping )

413
00:19:30,504 --> 00:19:32,439
- ( Avdol and boy gasp )
- jotaro: Hmph.

414
00:19:32,472 --> 00:19:34,441
D’arby: Ca...

415
00:19:34,474 --> 00:19:35,775
Avdol: That’s unbelievable!

416
00:19:35,809 --> 00:19:38,312
his eyes rolled
into the back of his head!

417
00:19:38,345 --> 00:19:39,813
( Boy gasps )
How is it possible

418
00:19:39,847 --> 00:19:42,450
for someone to faint
while they’re on their feet?

419
00:19:42,482 --> 00:19:43,917
Jotaro: He’s completely lost it.

420
00:19:43,951 --> 00:19:45,686
The pressure was too much.

421
00:19:45,719 --> 00:19:46,720
( Boy and avdol gasp )

422
00:19:51,258 --> 00:19:53,727
Avdol: Mr. Joestar
and polnareff’s souls

423
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:56,429
are returning to their bodies!
Thank heavens.

424
00:19:56,463 --> 00:19:59,232
( Both groaning )

425
00:19:59,266 --> 00:20:01,735
jotaro: Mentally,
he’s already forfeited the game.

426
00:20:01,768 --> 00:20:04,504
Deep down, he knew he had lost.

427
00:20:04,538 --> 00:20:06,640
that’s why
the souls were released.

428
00:20:06,673 --> 00:20:09,309
Avdol: F-four kings?!

429
00:20:09,343 --> 00:20:12,012
are you telling me
he had four kings all along?

430
00:20:12,045 --> 00:20:15,282
jotaro, I have to know
what cards you had in your hand

431
00:20:15,315 --> 00:20:16,416
to inspire such confidence.

432
00:20:16,450 --> 00:20:18,619
( Both gasp )

433
00:20:20,621 --> 00:20:21,889
Boy: Like I thought...

434
00:20:21,922 --> 00:20:23,690
( Avdol groans )

435
00:20:23,724 --> 00:20:26,894
Boy: Your hand was shit,
absolute shit!

436
00:20:26,927 --> 00:20:28,729
Jotaro: Even with
star platinum’s

437
00:20:28,762 --> 00:20:30,998
incredible speed, he wouldn’t
have been able to swap cards

438
00:20:31,031 --> 00:20:33,333
in front of an expert gambler
like d’arby.

439
00:20:33,367 --> 00:20:36,637
It’s a good thing my bluff
and intimidation worked so well

440
00:20:36,670 --> 00:20:38,038
with such a worthless hand.

441
00:20:38,071 --> 00:20:40,407
good grief.
Had I known it was this crappy,

442
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,875
I would have freaked.

443
00:20:41,909 --> 00:20:43,944
Avdol: What? What do you mean
you’d have freaked?!

444
00:20:43,977 --> 00:20:45,445
Jotaro, don’t tell me

445
00:20:45,479 --> 00:20:47,948
that you bet our souls
on that worthless hand!

446
00:20:47,981 --> 00:20:49,382
Joseph and polnareff: Eh?

447
00:20:49,416 --> 00:20:52,019
( D’arby laughing )

448
00:21:04,064 --> 00:21:05,499
Avdol: It would appear as though

449
00:21:05,532 --> 00:21:07,901
his collection of souls
has been released.

450
00:21:07,935 --> 00:21:11,405
D’arby: Come on, everyone!
Let’s play a game of mahjong!

451
00:21:11,438 --> 00:21:13,774
( Laughing )
Backgammon is a lot of fun, too!

452
00:21:13,807 --> 00:21:17,844
Or we could play a game of dice,
even though I don’t have any!

453
00:21:17,878 --> 00:21:20,914
Narrator: D’arby of
the osiris stand, retired.

454
00:21:20,948 --> 00:21:22,082
( D’arby laughing, babbling )

455
00:21:22,115 --> 00:21:23,850
Avdol: I doubt
that we’ll be able

456
00:21:23,884 --> 00:21:26,320
to pry dio’s secret
out of him in this state.

457
00:21:26,353 --> 00:21:28,789
jotaro: That’s true.
He was a formidable opponent.

458
00:21:28,822 --> 00:21:30,424
It’s humbling to admit this,

459
00:21:30,457 --> 00:21:32,592
but he almost took us all out
singlehandedly.

460
00:21:32,626 --> 00:21:35,362
The guy was a force
to be reckoned with.

461
00:21:35,395 --> 00:21:37,430
avdol: Indeed,
he was a fierce adversary.

462
00:21:37,464 --> 00:21:39,733
( Polnareff groans )
I feel like death warmed over.

463
00:21:39,766 --> 00:21:42,335
Joseph: Well,
I guess we can’t be

464
00:21:42,369 --> 00:21:44,438
the heroes in every episode.

465
00:21:46,807 --> 00:21:48,876
( Iggy barks )

466
00:21:49,877 --> 00:21:51,879
♪

